Who Are You?

The caravan has crawled across weeks of bitter miles, wheels grinding in ruts of dust and stone. Countless cold nights, thin meals, and the dry stink of pack beasts and old leather.

At long last, you stand before the gates of Aldgate, among weathered crates and trade cloth and dusty barrels. The caravan master is arguing with clerks in flat imperial livery. He looks to you for help, but you don't meet his gaze. You'll have trouble enough on your own in the city; this man can sort his own affairs.

The delay stretches on, and the caravan idles in the road like a beast made to kneel. Nothing moves but the wind worrying the banners above the gate and the restless shifting of pack mules. Your hand strays to your finger, still not quite used to the weight that rides there. The band sits heavy and unfamiliar against the bone. You ease it free and turn it slowly in the light, studying the seal as though it might explain itself.

A signet ring, gold, weathered from years of use. The ring has stamped contracts, treaties, death sentences. It opens doors for the bearer, loosens tongues, carries the grim authority of the Trade Guild.

How did you come by this ring?

choices:

* Murder = I took it by force
  The fat bastard bled more than you'd expected. You still feel the spray of it when you close your eyes, still see his hand twitching in that alley muck. The Guild will gut you for this theft if they catch you, but the borderlands are a lawless place. A land of blood and gold and shadow, and you were born for all three.
  +set_skill combat 4
  +set_skill bushcraft 2
  +set_skill cunning 2
  +open 01_Gameplay_Intro

* Birthright = My mother once wore this, but it is now mine
  This was your mother's ring, and she wielded it like a blade. Grim, dangerous men bent when its seal pressed wax. You remember the smell of hot resin and sea-salt in her hair, the way she would turn the signet once before a bargain, as if testing the world's grain for weakness. She said the ring would secure the family's future, and you mean to see that through.
  +set_skill negotiation 4
  +set_skill luck 2
