* Gambling = I won it in a game
  You still remember the trader's face when you called his bluff; the way his confidence shattered as you laid down your cards. The whole den had gone silent, unsure of what this meant. The man had thought a Guild signet would cow a room of dockside rabble, but you've always had the devil's luck. Now his ruin buys your passage to Aldgate, where your luck will surely unlock even greater fortunes.
