  +open 01_Gameplay_Intro

* A Gift = It was given to me
  The girl was nearly starved and half-mad when you found her, crouched beneath the roots of a storm-felled cedar. Her father's finest hunters gave up the search after the first week, but not you. You followed the broken language of the forest, the snapped twigs, the hush of disturbed birds, the faint drag-marks, and you found her. Later, in a hall heavy with smoke and gratitude, her father presented you with his ring. As folks tell the story, he is the noble and selfless father, and you are a nameless hunter. You've come here to make your own story, where your name will be remembered.
  +set_skill cunning 2
  +set_skill bushcraft 4
  +set_skill combat 2
  +open 01_Gameplay_Intro

* A Commission = The Guild sent me
  The ring is yours. Not stolen, not inherited, not won; earned. Twelve years in the Guild's cartography corps, charting coastlines and trade routes from the Pale Reach to the Saffron Delta. You've bled for every league of parchment, fought off things in uncharted places that don't appear on any map because you decided they shouldn't. When the Guild needed someone to survey a rough land they chose you. The commission came with the signet, the authority to requisition supplies and act in the Guild's name. You intend to draw the definitive map of this place. If you happen to turn a profit along the way, well. You are Guild, after all.
  +set_skill combat 4
  +set_skill bushcraft 2
  +set_skill cunning 2
